Description:
This is the first epic in Indian Music History, I think. Every single song.

Dilka alam main kya batau tujhe, ek cheherene bahut pyar se dekha mujhe....

Jaane jigar jaaneman, tujhko hai meri kasam, tujo mujhe na mila marjaungi main sanam... janam jaane jaa... oh what a song.

Main dunya bhula dunga tere chahat main...

Bass ek sanam chahiye ashiqui ke liye...

Nazar ke samne jigar paas koi rehta hai woh ho tum...

Dheere dheere se mere zindagi mein ana, dheere dheere se dilko churana...

Abtere bin jeelenge hum, zeher zindagi ka peelenge hum... one of the greatest broken heart songs.

And my personal favorite: Tu... meri zindagi hai... tu... meri har khushi hai, tuhi pyar tuhi chaaat, tuhi ashiqi hai... Pehli mohabbat ka ehsas hai tu.. bujhke jo bujhna payi woh pyas hai tu...

The music was a cult hit and the hairstyle of [link=nm0747149]. It was called Rahul cutting in Bangladesh's most of the saloon.

Introducing the voice of [link=nm0764384].

Introducing mega-hit by Nadeem Shravan.

Tumhein Apna Banaane Ki... [link=nm0764384]

Jab jab pyar pe pehra hua hai, pyar aur bhi gehra, gehra, gehra, gehra hua hai...

Our first audio cd cassette when I was in class 6 may be, it was 1998. It was the only cd cassette we had that time so listening to this was a daily routine. I miss those days a lot.

The movie was also a cult hit because of its music from Nadeem-Shravan and the villain, cult villain in the history of Bollywood, [link=nm0025389].
